The paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep feature-based image retrieval systems, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for unsupervised learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the manipulation of deep neural networks, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The concept of adversarial attacks could also be relevant to the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions various application scenarios, including person Re-ID and face search, which could suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
